text.tspan: Key Bank BNPL Developments:
Company
Commentary
BFH
Partnered with ChargeAfter, an embedded lending / point-of-sale financing platform, to add Bread Pay pay-over-time
options into ChargeAfter’s lender network
C
-195 merchants on PoS platform as of 2024
-Citi Flex Pay added as a checkout option when using Apple Pay to split purchases of $75 or more into fixed monthly
payments and offers virtual credit card (Citi Pay Credit) but not typical PoS solutions offered at merchant level
JPM
-JPMorgan Payments struck a deal with Klarna to embed Klarna’s BNPL / flexible-financing options into JPM’s
Commerce Solutions / merchant services platform
- Affirm announced a deal to integrate its installment / BNPL offering as a checkout option for merchants leveraging
JPMorgan’s payments infrastructure
SYF
- Amazon shows a “Pay Later with Synchrony” option that lets approved customers split purchases into installments
(generally on carts of $50+).
-PayPal added a physical credit card to extend its financing (e.g., promo periods) to in-store purchases; the card is
issued by Synchrony and pairs with Mastercard’s network.
CFG
- Noted that BNPL is small part of loan portfolio (~$2bn) with some blue chip partners (44 as of 2022)
USB
- Offers BNPL thorugh Elavon merchant subsidiary
-ExtendPay (not PoS) allows consumers/business to split credit card purchaes into monthly payments
AXP
- Embedded a capability called Pay Over Time on 92% of charge portfolio
- More of a back-end feature to allow customers to manage existing balances, allowing consumers capacity to revolve
